Please note that the code of good practice for movie reviews recommends that critical reviews should:
1. Focus on the artistic and entertainment value of the film; 
2. Avoid plot and character spoilers;
3. Include positive elements that the film has;
4. Reflect diverse voices and viewpoints;
5. Encourage discussion and debate on the artistic merits of the film;
6. Keep writing focused on the themes, messages and ideas in the film.

Also you can use the recommended Invision forum post settings

- Movie should be in spoiler tags if review/spoiler contains plot or character elements that could ruin the movie experience of some users.
- Use ***SPOILER ALERT*** tag if warning is needed.
- Use clearly defined spoiler tags for major plot points in movies, but try to avoid using these where possible.

Please review your post and make sure it meets the Do’s and Don’ts listed above so we can better help you.
